data.meta_description: Approach Tyne and Wear by rail or motorway from the south and you know you are nearly there when you spot that most surreal of sights, the Angel of the North. Designed by Antony Gormley, this industrial-sized steel sculpture stands proud on the edge of Low Fell in Gateshead.
data.text:
World Guide to Newcastle, England

Newcastle has recently been voted the UK's best short break destinations and Newcastle is considered one of the world's new cultural Meccas, with many attractions. Newcastle city has more listed buildings than any other UK city. World Guide to Sunderland, England

Sunderland was once a city of industry, with bustling docks and productive coal mines. Nowadays, the appearance of Sunderland is quite different. This is now a modern city with attractive coastal scenery and some easily accessible beaches.
